postgres

> Install 
	> sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib

> Config
	> create first data base
		> sudo -u postgres psql
		CREATE DATABASE xyz;
	> create user
		> this should be the name of your account so that you can automatically login
		> CREATE USER xyz WITH PASSWORD 'abc';
	
for django set up instructions see django

open shell for specific database
	> psql <database name>

commands : in psql shell
	> \dt
		> shows tables of the database you are looking at
	> \d+ <table name>
		> shows table fields
	> \du
		> shows users on database